      <h1>CSS Minifier vs CSS Beautifier: When to Compress, When to Expand</h1>

      <p>CSS minification and CSS beautification are inverse operations that serve different stages of the development lifecycle. Minification strips whitespace, comments, and redundant characters to reduce file size for production. Beautification adds indentation and formatting to make CSS readable for development and debugging. Understanding when to apply each operation is essential for an efficient front-end workflow.</p>

